runBacktest().details: Tests which parameter combinations would have been most successful historically

runCompleteAnalysis().details: Demonstrates the typical workflow for analyzing arbitrage opportunities

runSensitivityAnalysis().details: Shows how profit changes with different gas prices and loan premiums

devdoc.details: Performs statistical analysis on historical trade data and recommends parameters Does NOT execute trades or interact with DEXs

params.gasPrices: Array of gas prices used in each trade
params.trades: Historical trade data with gas information

returns._0: Array of BacktestResult for each combination

params.leg1AmountOut: Expected output from first leg in Wei
params.leg2AmountOut: Expected output from second leg in Wei

params.priceRatio: Expected ratio of leg2Out / leg1Out (in PRECISION)
params.step: Step size for iteration in Wei

returns._0: OptimalBorrowResult with optimal amount and profitability

params.trades: Original trade data for slippage and execution time analysis

params.flashLoanPremiums: Array of flash loan premiums to test in BPS
params.gasPrices: Array of gas prices to test in Wei

returns._0: Array of SensitivityResult for each combination
